# Git guidelines

The canonical rule content lives in [`coding-rules/rules/git.md`](mdc:coding-rules/rules/git.md) — a single source of truth shared with Claude Code so the tools cannot drift.

For all version-control activity (commits, branches, pull requests), read and follow `coding-rules/rules/git.md`: atomic commits that pass at every step, imperative subject lines with the why in the body, mechanical changes separated from logic changes, `feature/*` / `fix/*` / `chore/*` branches, one concern per PR, and no rewriting of published history.
